Also, I would like to make sure that this is a bug and not by design. I will bring this up at the next irc meeting. I feel like this is a kind of thing that could break a bunch of automated scripts on top of Glance. No?

Patch Set 1:

Changing defaults is always risk of pain for users, even if the new default value is way better as in this case.

Can you kick off an ML discussion about this, just to give notice and a chance for anyone that might be harmed to voice their concerns? If no one complains on the ML too much, I'm +1.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

Allowing tenants to make images public by default is a major security risk.

A malicious tenant can easy add code to an image that can do harm to unsuspecting tenants.

In my opinion, default should be to not allow non admins to make images public and leave the decision to the admin.

Patch Set 1:

I agree that changing defaults is a pain; in this case I think it's probably worth it.

We should probably give a heads up to the TripleO folks in particular.

Patch Set 1:

I'll ping the ML about it.

(1 comment)

I was actually surprised when I read your mailing list post that the default policy was to allow anyone to post as is_public. I don't believe that it used to be that way, but I may be remembering code before the policy.json was introduced...

Anyway, +1 for changing to the more secure default.

Typo in commit message, BTW, but nothing to -1 about.

Best,

-jay
